They also have new things to chat about depending on the player's progress in the Civil War Imperial questline. ESPFE. Voiced by Elevenlabs AI.

Voiced via Elevenlabs AI. Updates to come!

State.Author: Valdaraak
State.Description: Makes default inns more immersive by adding varying room cost, innkeepers sleeping at night, and a chance that the inn will be full. Offers customizable prices, availability, and the ability to turn off certain features.
State.Name: Improved Innkeepers

State.Description: Removes the quest from Nordic Jewelry and distributes variations of metal and gem combination into levelled lists.

State.Author: Mihail and Eli Hartwood
State.Description: "Talkative Dragon Priests" adds 32 new immersive lines of custom dialogue to these powerful ancient undead enemies, making your battles against them more epic, frightening and unique.
State.Name: Talkative Dragon Priests- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail and Kiara Dougherty
State.Description: "Talkative Wispmothers" adds 12 new immersive lines of custom dialogue to these mysterious spirits of the wind and frost, making your battles against them more epic, frightening and unique.
State.Name: Talkative Wispmothers - Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: JaySerpa
State.Description: This mod makes NPCs smarter and capable of dealing with the most cheesy strategy Skyrim has ever seen: shooting NPCs from locations they cannot reach. They will now hide properly and relocate if necessary, while also shaming you for using dirty tactics (with 200+ voiced reactions!)
State.Name: NPCs Take Cover - Smarter Anti-Cheese AI

State.Author: JaySerpa
State.Description: Happy Birthday, Skyrim! Fish in third person! Fish in first person! Fish in... second person? Fish in Fish Person! OH, and new lines for the fishing quests and other fishing enhancements!
State.Name: Simple Fishing Overhaul - Animations and Improved Quest Dialogue

State.Author: JaySerpa
State.Description: Ever noticed how NPCs don't react at all to being woken up in the middle of the night? Or how characters stop breathing while they sleep? Or... how it takes them YEARS to get in and out of bed? Well, no more! WAKE UP, JARL BALGRUUF!!!!!!! Sleeping Expanded is here!!!!
State.Name: Sleeping Expanded - Animations and NPC reactions

State.Author: Voeille
State.Description: Ever found it weird that dragons, fully sapient beings, have never spoken a word while you’re doing your best trying to defeat them? This mod changes that.
State.Name: Talkative Dragons

State.Author: Mihail

I was heavily inspired by Viking art and the HBO series Game of Thrones( A Song of Ice and Fire book series), none of the cloaks in the mod

State.Name: Tel Mithryn Overhaul - High Poly and Improved Meshes

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: The Ancient Nordic Sentinels are a type of gigantic Foundation Stone Golem made of old norse architecture. Guardians of the ancient tombs, and the terror of their invaders, these fearsome colossi animated by the souls of powerful warriors will crush all foes with no mercy.
State.Name: Ancient Nordic Sentinel- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''golem'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: With this mod you will have adorable baby mammoths in your world, grazing alongside their mothers near the Giant camps.
State.Name: Baby Mammoths - Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: All Mihail's chicken and chick mods compiled in one esp. Replace the ugly vanilla chickens and even add new color varieties, plus adorable chicks following them around.
State.Name: Chickens and Chicks- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Crystal Golems are large masses of faceless and vaguely humanoid crystal, animated by unknown means, that patrol Blackreach. Despite Azura's Moonshadow and Meridia's Colored Rooms being almost inaccessible to mortals, it's certain that some roam that realms since they're often summoned on Nirn by azura's and meridia's worshipers.
State.Name: Crystal Golems - Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''dark souls'')

State.Author: Mihail and ED Hartwood
State.Description: The Xivilai who inhabit the Deadlands have an affinity for fire, and red markings scattered across their skin, grayer than their Coldharbour cousins. Like Dagon, they share a taste for destruction and insurrection, regarding other Xivilai clans as inferior, even shameful representatives of their kind.
State.Name: Deadlands Xivilais- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Bundle of Mihail's Draugr Cavalry and Draugr Patrols mods in one esp. The terrifying nordic undead will haunt your nightmares every night from now on after you install this mod.
State.Name: Draugr Patrols and Cavalry- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Compilation of Mihail's Classic Ghosts and Mourning Souls mods in one esp. Take Skyrim's spooky haunts to the next level with this terrifying add-on.
State.Name: Ghosts and Souls- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE) (''undead'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Complete overhaul of the vanilla Giants, diversifying the appearance of the males, and adding several variants of Giantesses and also a juvenile version. It never made sense that all Giants were male and looked exactly the same, so this mod is here to solve this problem once and for all.
State.Name: Giants Overhaul- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Now compiled into a single mod, the pesky Goblins and Riekrs clans will make your exploration of the world more interesting and challenging.
State.Name: Goblins and Riekrs- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Grahls and Frost Giant Overhaul in one file: these two mysterious beasts native to the most remote icy caverns of Skyrim and Solstheim are sure to provide unforgettable encounters when exploring the region's most inhospitable snowy peaks.
State.Name: Grahls and Frost Giants - Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: House cats are docile little felines, often kept as pets in towns and villages. Although initially domesticated to hunt rats that destroyed food and spread diseases, the excess of pampering and treats made most city cats have chubby bodies and lazy behavior. In Skyrim, you'll encounter them in almost every city and farm.
State.Name: House Cats- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''pet'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Indriks are feathered magical deer-like creatures that bear some direct relation to Y'ffre. Indriks fight using elemental-based attacks, with power drawn from the very Earth Bones beneath their hooves. Relentless protectors of nature, a wild Indrik will not hesitate to slaughter anyone he deems to be a potential danger to the wild world.
State.Name: Indriks- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''eso'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Compilation of Mihail's Kagouti and Guars mods in one esp. A mod that can't be missing from any Morrowind lover's load order.
State.Name: Kagoutis and Guars- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''morrowind'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Now in a single mod, Mimics and Oozes are fearsome and sneaky living traps that lurk in the darkest corners waiting to devour adventurers in search for fame and fortune. With this mod, exploring and looting dungeons will never be a safe experience again.
State.Name: Mimics and Oozes- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: These dangerous and solitary predatory felines are fast, agile and, like all cats, devilishly cunning. Whether in surprise ambush attacks or head-to-head confrontations, the sharp claws and powerful jaws of one of these panthers is always a force to be reckoned with.
State.Name: Mountain Lions and Panthers- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Ograts are tiny vermin rodents that inhabit the desolate ruins of the Ashpit, Malacath's Oblivion realm. Their body is covered by an exoskeleton that protects them from the harsh conditions of this place. Orcs like to keep Ograts as pets in their Strongholds, permanently summoned to Nirn.
State.Name: Ograts- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

Original.Name: Old Gods of the Hunt (SE) 1.4.1 version-27520-1-4-1-1651832785.rar

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: The Old Gods of the Hunt are powerfull and mysterious ancient creatures from a previous Wild Hunt, that still roams through Tamriel in very small numbers in the current era. Ferocious and stunning powerfull, this Wild Hunt beasts are connected to Hircine, and worshiped since the beginning by the Reachmen and the Bosmer as one of their Old Gods.
State.Name: Old Gods of the Hunt- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''the witcher'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Both of these gigantic races that inspired some of the most terrifying sailor stories are now compiled in one mod. The shores of Skyrim will become a dangerous place to cross, even for the bravest pirate.
State.Name: Sea Giants and Ice Titans- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: This large feline is a relentless predator, even managing to take down Mammoths of considerable size when hunting in groups. Although the term is also used to define all members of the most well-known and abundant feline family of saber-toothed predators, it is the largest among these that is usually individually referred to as Smilodon.
State.Name: Smilodon- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''megafauna'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Sprites are timid nature spirits resembling small floating orbs, usually blue in color, with two pairs of transparent wings. They produce a sparkling, magical sound and pose no danger. Several stories tell of heroes who were guided by Sprites during their journeys until they reached their goals.
State.Name: Sprites- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''fairy'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Thri-Kreen are mutated ritualistic warriors created by Falmer alchemy using the Chaurus creature as a base. These obedient humanoid insects outperform the own Falmers in physical capacities, and do not need to rest, being excellent defenders of the hives where they live. They are also commonly used to protect the valuable Shellbugs.
State.Name: Thri-Kreen Warriors and Shellbugs- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)(''falmer'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Even the smallest and most harmless fish of the Shivering Isles embody the strangeness and insanity of their creator. Whether they were created by a simple egocentric whim of Sheogorath, or even to kindly fulfill a request from his subordinates, it is questionable whether these fish truly appreciate the mutations they have undergone.
State.Name: Veiltail Lobsterfish and Emean Triclops- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: The wolves that inhabit Cyrodiil are smaller than their nordic cousins, however, these pack predators prove to be just as efficient as their larger relatives. They can be found in Skyrim mainly near the border with their home province, with some packs migrating to regions further north.
State.Name: Wolves of Cyrodiil - Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)
